name: sfchronicle
text:
Former Republican presidential nominee Mitt Romney condemned President Trump's unsubstantiated claims of election fraud Friday. 

The president “is wrong to say the election was rigged, corrupt and stolen,” the Utah senator tweeted. https://t.co/5ZTLsgUFo3

name: sfchronicle
text: Parts of the Bay Area could finally see some long-awaited rain Friday afternoon. https://t.co/YvtP1HJhRX

name: sfchronicle
text:
A limited selection of rides and outdoor arcade games will open at the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk on Nov. 7. 

But there's a catch: No tourists will be allowed on the rides. https://t.co/ByH1UW8kJA

name: sfchronicle
text: RT @ronkroichick: Alabama's Najee Harris is shedding SEC tacklers the way he dominated high school kids during his Antioch days. My story on Harris' strong senior season and his path to becoming the Crimson Tide's all-time leading rusher: https://t.co/Gh6uI8CMlr

name: sfchronicle
text:

text:

text:
The latest round of looting on — which police believe is an attempt to capitalize on possible election-related unrest — targeted a Richmond shoe store, an Emeryville drug store, a San Leandro convenience store and a San Lorenzo sporting goods store.

name: sfchronicle
text:
RT @meganrcassidy: Scott Peterson today waived his right to a speedy death-penalty retrial, which was scheduled for later this month. 

He's holding out to see whether a judge finds the entire case should be retried due to an impartial juror.

name: sfchronicle
text: All around the Bay Area, restaurateurs are adding roofs to parklets, tents to patios and heaters by tables in the hopes of combating rain and chill — in one case spending as much as $10,000 a month to rent equipment. https://t.co/Avugigmmug
